[1] Philippines (Metro Manila)
Date: Mon 16 Jun 2008
Source: GMA News.TV [edited]
<http://www.gmanews.tv/story/101332/Dengue-cases-up-100-in-Caloocan---report>


Health officials in Caloocan City have recorded a 100-percent
increase in dengue cases in the 1st 5 months of 2008, compared to the
same period last year [2007].

Radio dzBB's Bernie Morales reported that city health officer Claire
Clemente said they recorded 630 cases from 1 Jan-29 May [2008]. Of
the 630 cases, 5 died. Clemente said most of the dengue victims were males.

She said the city government is now stepping up its information
campaign against dengue, now that the rainy season is approaching.

Health authorities consider dengue a year-round threat, and have
advised the public to keep their surroundings dry and clean to
prevent dengue-carrying mosquitoes from breeding

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur A-Lan Banks

[A map showing the location of Caloocan City in Metro Manila can be accessed at
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caloocan_City>. - Mod.TY]

