[4] Indonesia (South Kalimantan)
Date: Fri 13 Jun 2008
Source: Republika [in Indonesian, machine trans., edited]
<http://republika.co.id/online_detail.asp?id=337578&kat_id=23>


During the period January-May 2008, 260 residents of South Kalimantan
Province were afflicted by dengue fever, including 6 who died.

"We continued to carry out the step-by-step control in anticipation
and in order to be able to press forward against the increase of the
number of sufferers all over the area including 13 cities/regencies,"
said the South Kalimantan Health official, Rosihan Adhani.

The number of recorded South Kalimantan residents who contracted
dengue in 2007 was 1000 people spread over 13 cities/regencies in
South Kalimantan. Of these, 6 died.

Government officials continue to push residents to clean up
mosquito-breeding sites and trash in order to control the vector
mosquito. Other control efforts continue to be carried out by
counselling about the signs of early dengue fever illness, to be able
to detect [infection] early so that [these early cases] could be
treated quickly, both through the community health centres and in the
hospitals in order to avoid death, said Rosihan Adhani.

--
