[6] Brazil (Minas Gerais)
Date: Wed 4 Jun 2008
Source: O Globo Online [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://oglobo.globo.com/pais/mat/2008/06/04/confirmada_terceira_morte_por_dengue_em_belo_horizonte-546647651.asp>



Physicians and health professionals in Belo Horizonte have been put
on alert for the evolution of clinically severe dengue [virus
infections]. Despite the decrease in the number of [dengue] cases,
the disease is more aggressive. This Wednesday [4 Jun 2008], the
municipal Secretariat of Health confirmed the 3rd dengue death this
year [2008] in the municipality. According to the results of
examinations revealed this Wednesday [4 Jun 2008], the victim died of
complications resulting from classical dengue.

The Belo Horizonte secretary of health, Helvecio Magalhaes, denied
that there was a delay in providing the information resulting from
the examination, and affirmed that there have been no other deaths
under investigation that were suspected to be due to the disease
[dengue]. In 2007, 7875 classical dengue cases were confirmed in the
capital, 16 cases of complicated [dengue] cases, and 5 DHF (dengue
hemorrhagic fever) cases.

--
