[7] Brazil (Bahia)
Date: Sat 14 Jun 2008
Source: Correio da Bahia [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.correiodabahia.com.br/aquisalvador/noticia.asp?codigo=155628>


In the past 72 hours, 2 people suspected of having DHF died in the
Manoel Novaes Hospital, in Itabuna.

Up to the present, there have been 6 [dengue-related] deaths in the
state and, with the new victims the number increases to 4 suspected
cases that await the results of tests for evidence [of dengue virus infection].

According to the coordinator of endemics of the municipal Secretariat
of Health of Itabuna, Jose Roberto Goes, this year [2008], 904 dengue
cases have been reported in the city. Of this total, there were only
189 with laboratory test results with confirmation of 29 cases. The 2
deaths created a climate of fear in the municipality. Starting on
Monday [16 Jun 2008] the Municipal Secretariat of Health of Itabuna
will make available an area in the Annex to Hospital Sao Lucas in
order to attend to patients with suspected dengue.

Despite the measure, the secretary Jesuino Oliveira says that the
municipality does not face an alarming situation. He warns, however,
that it is necessary that the population help combat the mosquito. "I
do not see an outbreak concern, but it is important that the
population becomes aware of the need for necessary care, " Jesuino
Oliveira stressed.

The latest index of [_Aedes aegypti_ vector mosquito] infestation in
the municipality is from April 2008, when it reached 7.67 percent.
The municipal secretariat should provide the data for the month of
May next week [week of 22 Jun 2008].

--
