[8] Brazil (Ceara)
Date: Sat 14 Jun 2008
Source: O Povo [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.opovo.com.br/opovo/fortaleza/796550.html>


Classical dengue now counts 25 836 laboratory confirmed cases this
year [2008], distributed in 159 of the 184 Ceara municipalities.
According to the weekly bulletin issued by the state Secretariat of
Health, from 1 Jan-June 2008], 318 cases were recorded as DHF with 10
deaths and 292 were cases of dengue fever with complications with 21
deaths. There are 242 cases under investigation with 21 deaths, 12 of
which occurred in Fortaleza.

The number of dengue [cases] in Ceara in 2008 is now greater than in
last year [2007], with a total of 25 026 classical [dengue] cases and
298 DHF [cases].

In Fortaleza thee have been 16 646 laboratory confirmed cases, 165
recorded DHF cases with 6 deaths, and 184 cases of dengue with complications.

--
